en: Gift of Helen Tudor Robinson, 1960. Formerly in the Collection of Edward P. Warren at Lewes, then the D.M. Robinson collection, inv. no. 217.
Broken and mended, restored in 1981 at the Fogg Art Museum Conservation Laboratory.
H. 0.116 m.; D rim 0.29 - 0.295 m.; W with handles 0.380 m.; D foot 0.107 m.
Incised on the handle is the signature of the potter *I*E*R*O*N *E*P*O*I*E*S*E*N ("Hieron made [me]"). The signature has been doubted.
CVA, Robinson Collection 3, USA 7, 15, pl. 4; LIMC, III, pl. 353, Dionysos 469
